<XMLDocContent PageName="cobalt.graphics.IStateGroupNode.SetComputeTask" Title="SetComputeTask method" xmlns="http://www.cobaltrenderer.com/schema/XMLDocSchema.xsd">
  <Paragraph>
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.graphics.Welcome">Home</PageRef> ->
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.graphics.IStateGroupNode">IStateGroupNode</PageRef> ->
    SetComputeTask
  </Paragraph>
  <Section Title="Description">
    <Paragraph>
      The <TypeRef>SetComputeTask</TypeRef> method defines a compute task to execute for this node. No child nodes or rendering state settings are valid when a compute task is defined, and the parent IShaderProgram node must define a compute shader.
    </Paragraph>
  </Section>
  <Section Title="Usage">
    <Code Language="C++"><![CDATA[void SetComputeTask(const V3UInt32& threadGroupCounts);]]></Code>
    <SubSection Title="Argument list">
      <ArgumentList>
        <ArgumentListEntry Type="const V3UInt32" Name="threadGroupCounts">
          The number of compute shader thread groups to dispatch in the X, Y, and Z dimensions.
        </ArgumentListEntry>
      </ArgumentList>
    </SubSection>
  </Section>
  <Section Title="See also">
    <PageRefList>
      <PageRefListEntry PageName="cobalt.graphics.IStateGroupNode">IStateGroupNode</PageRefListEntry>
    </PageRefList>
  </Section>
</XMLDocContent>
